HEADWORD: Unblind
<hw>Un*blind"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>blind</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from blindness;
to give or restore sight to; to open the eyes of.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>J. Webster (1607).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

